title.narrative: IMMUNIZATION COVERAGE > 90%

description.narrative: By 2018, at least 80% of health districts in Congo have immunization coverage for all vaccines >90%, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Immunization, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2018, at least 90 % of pregnant women, U5 children living in the targeted most vulnerable areas have access and utilize package of high impact interventions for their survival

title.narrative: By 2018, at least 80% of health districts in Congo have immunization coverage for all vaccines >90%

description.narrative: In 2019, joint efforts of UNICEF, WHO, GAVI and Government enabled to strengthen routine immunization in terms of cold chain, vaccine supply and reach every child. As result, vaccine coverage increased for all antigens. Vaccine coverage of DTP3 increased from 75 per cent in 2018 to 79 per cent as of October 2019.The equity focus is illustrated by the decrease of the number of low-performance districts (coverage vaccine less than 50 percent) from nine to five, a reduction of 55 per cent. | Status:Met | As-of Date:05/02/2020
